<h4>Handwriting</h4>
<p>When you write in English you can print out your letters one at a time, which is easy to read, but can be slow, 
or you can use "joined up writing", also called "cursive script", which is quicker to write, but can be difficult to read if your handwriting is bad. </p>
<p>Print your letters one at a time. </p>
<p>or</p>
<p><span class="cursive"><font size="6">Write using cursive script.</font>
</span>  </p>
<p>A good sentence for practising your handwriting is:</p>
<p>"The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog."</p>
