<td bgcolor="#FFFF80" align="center">      <p>The average English person will say please and thank you at least <b><i>200</i></b> times a day. </p>
        <p>We even have a saying, "Mind your ps and qs."</p>
        <p>If you don't say "please" when asking for something, someone might say, "What's the magic word?"</p>
        <p>You can even say, "Pretty please."<br>
                <br>
                "Thanks" and "ta" are very informal.<br>
                <br>
                In the UK, "You're welcome" is a common response to "Thank you".</p>
        <p>In the US, "No problem", is a common response to "Thank you".</p></td>
